From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ws63-rs <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 16:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] hw/riscv: register the HiSilicon BS22 machine (minimal/M1)

Build-system integration for hw/riscv/bs22.c (the minimal BS22 / BS2X machine,
copied into the tree alongside this series). Like bs21.c, bs22.c reuses the
shared HiSilicon riscv31 device models from ws63.c via hisi_riscv31.h, so
CONFIG_BS22 selects CONFIG_WS63 (which compiles ws63.c and the shared models).

BS22 is register- and memory-identical to BS21E at the milestone-1 level (the
whole BS2X family shares platform_core.h peripheral bases + chip_core_irq.h IRQ
numbers, and BS22's M1 memory map matches BS21E's 160K L2RAM layout), so the same
bare-metal bs2x firmware (examples/bs21/{blinky,uart_hello}) boots on -M bs22.

Adds the CONFIG_BS22 meson source entry and the Kconfig symbol (default y on
RISCV32, selects UNIMP + WS63). Registers `-M bs22`.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 hw/riscv/Kconfig     | 7 +++++++
 hw/riscv/meson.build | 1 +
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+)
diff --git a/hw/riscv/Kconfig b/hw/riscv/Kconfig
--- a/hw/riscv/Kconfig
+++ b/hw/riscv/Kconfig
@@ -132,3 +132,10 @@
     depends on RISCV32
     select UNIMP
     select WS63
+
+config BS22
+    bool
+    default y
+    depends on RISCV32
+    select UNIMP
+    select WS63
diff --git a/hw/riscv/meson.build b/hw/riscv/meson.build
--- a/hw/riscv/meson.build
+++ b/hw/riscv/meson.build
@@ -16,4 +16,5 @@
 
 riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_WS63', if_true: files('ws63.c'))
 riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_BS21', if_true: files('bs21.c'))
+riscv_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_BS22', if_true: files('bs22.c'))
 hw_arch += {'riscv': riscv_ss}
